# OpenCode Setup and Operations

This project includes an OpenCode-first workflow when `with_opencode = true`.

## Configuration Layers

This template enforces a **project-only configuration policy** for reproducibility.
All OpenCode behavior is defined in version-controlled project files:

| # | Layer | Source | Managed Here? |
|---|-------|--------|:-------------:|
| 1 | Project config | `opencode.json` | **Yes** |
| 2 | Project folders | `.opencode/` → `agents/`, `commands/`, `plugins/`, `skills/` | **Yes** |

Repository policy: do not rely on remote organization defaults or global user
config as required inputs for this project.

The `.opencode` directory uses plural names for subdirectories:
`agents/`, `commands/`, `modes/`, `plugins/`, `skills/`, `tools/`, and `themes/`.

## What This Template Configures

### Project Config (`opencode.json`)

- Default model: **OpenAI GPT-5 Mini** (`openai/gpt-5-mini`)
- Small model: auto-detected from active provider (omit to let OpenCode choose)
- Multi-provider ready (GitHub Copilot, OpenAI, Anthropic, OpenRouter)
- Remote MCP servers: `context7` (docs search), `gh_grep` (GitHub snippet search)
- Formatters: `ruff` (Python), `prettier` (TypeScript/JS/JSON/CSS/Markdown)
- Compaction: auto-enabled with pruning (10K token reserve)
- TUI preferences: scroll acceleration, auto diff style
- Least-privilege permissions with explicit allow/deny rules

