#### GSD-2 Quick Start

```bash
# Install globally (requires Node.js 20+)
npm install -g gsd-pi

# Or run via npx without global install
npx gsd-pi@latest --version

# First-time setup wizard (LLM provider + tool keys)
gsd config

# Verify
gsd headless doctor
```

GSD reads its preferences from `.gsd/preferences.md` (project-level config).
It coexists with this template's agents/commands.

**Core workflow**: `gsd` → `/gsd` (step mode) or `/gsd auto` (autonomous mode)
→ `/gsd status` (check progress) → `Ctrl+Alt+G` (dashboard overlay)

**Additional commands**: `/gsd discuss`, `/gsd quick`, `/gsd doctor`, `/gsd queue`, `/gsd steer`, `/gsd forensics`, `/gsd keys`, `/gsd update`, `/gsd export --html --all`.

**Verification**: Preferences define `verification_commands` that run after each task.
On failure, `verification_auto_fix` attempts automatic repair up to `verification_max_retries` times.

**Preferences**: Model assignments, timeouts, budget ceiling, token profiles, verification, auto-report, and git isolation
are configured in `.gsd/preferences.md` — managed interactively via `/gsd prefs`.

**Per-project MCP**: `.gsd/mcp.json` configures project-scoped MCP servers for GSD-2 (mirrors `opencode.json` MCP config).

#### OpenAgents Control (OAC) Quick Start

```bash
# Install (one command — installs OAC + OpenCode CLI if missing)
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/darrenhinde/OpenAgentsControl/main/install.sh | bash -s developer

# Or interactive install
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/darrenhinde/OpenAgentsControl/main/install.sh -o install.sh
bash install.sh

# Run agents
opencode --agent OpenAgent
# Or for code-focused tasks:
opencode --agent OpenCoder
```

OAC extends OpenCode with pattern-controlled AI development:
- **ContextScout**: Discovers project coding standards before generating code
- **Approval gates**: Agents propose changes, you approve, agents execute
- **MVI principle**: Reduces token usage via Minimal Viable Information design
- **Team patterns**: Store in `.opencode/context/project/`, commit to repo, shared across the team
- **Editable agents**: Configured via markdown files (`nano .opencode/agent/core/opencoder.md`)
- **3 main agents**: OpenAgent (general), OpenCoder (production), SystemBuilder (custom AI systems)
- **7+ subagents**: ContextScout, TaskManager, CoderAgent, TestEngineer, CodeReviewer, BuildAgent, ExternalScout
- **Commands**: `/add-context`, `/commit`, `/test`, `/optimize`, `/context`

**Scaffolded context files** (in `.opencode/context/project/`) — pre-populated for ContextScout:
- `coding-standards.md` — Project coding standards and conventions
- `architecture.md` — Architecture overview, layer boundaries, key files
- `workflow-patterns.md` — Development workflow, git strategy, task runner

**Update OAC**: `curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/darrenhinde/OpenAgentsControl/main/update.sh | bash`

